news.title: China: Longfor Group Holdings shares plunge after chairwoman resigns
news.para: Longfor also said its controlling shareholder, Charm Talent International Limited, had bought 3 million shares in the company at HK$9.53 a piece, as well as $5 million in principal of the 3.375% senior notes due 2027, on the open market during the session.

news.title: Shriram Properties & ASK Property Fund set up Rs 500 crore residential real estate platform
news.para: Shriram Properties and ASK Property Fund will co-invest in plotted and residential developments projects in Bengaluru, Chennai, and Hyderabad.

news.title: West Bengal: 23 Bowbazar buildings first off block for rebuilding
news.para: ​​Three more buildings damaged on May 11 are being razed at Durga Pituri Lane, right next to the open space where the 23 houses stood before the 2019 tunnelling disaster.

news.title: Guwahati civic body to issue SOP to stop piling up of construction materials on roadsides
news.para: Dahal said the GMC is currently imposing a small amount of penalty as “a symbolic enforcement”, so that people become aware of its harmful impact and avoid such a practice.

news.title: Establish an urban industrial township authority in Mysuru, demand stakeholders
news.para: ​​Industrialists pointed to the lack of basic infrastructure and amenities in several of these areas, although they were dutifully paying tax to the civic agencies.

news.title: About 16 more bajri mining leases issued in Rajasthan
news.para: "The approval will end the scarcity of sand for the construction of houses and buildings, and 90 percent of the total demand of the entire state would be met,” said additional chief secretary (mines) Subodh Agrawal.

news.title: Bhopal civic body issues notices to 800 property tax defaulters
news.para: BMC moves comes at the end of the concession period on October 31. Effective recovery of dues is planned by BMC. By identifying 50 ‘big defaulters’ for each ward directions for attachment of properties or closure of shops has been mandated.

news.title: CBRI develops 'affordable' smart face mask for construction workers
news.para: The researchers said the smart face mask gives pure air for breathing to users as it has multi-layer filters such as electrostatic, HEPA and laser arrangements.

news.title: Delhi: 586 teams formed to ensure implementation of ban on construction work
news.para: The Commission for Air Quality Management (CAQM) has directed the authorities in the NCR to implement curbs, including a ban on construction and demolition activities, under stage III of the Graded Response Action Plan, Rai said.

news.title: Despite curbs, construction in full swing in many areas in Gurugram
news.para: Spot visits to multiple locations such as Sector 7, Sadar Bazaar, Pataudi road, and New Railway Road, among others, revealed that many contractors were unaware of the ban and were awaiting directions from their seniors and civic authorities.

news.title: Will first bring down delinquency in corporate loans before restarting finance: PNB Housing
news.para: In the second quarter ended September 2022, the company's corporate loan book share reduced to 10 per cent with an exposure of Rs 5,708 crore. The retail segment loan book stood at Rs 52,124 crore, constituting 90 per cent of its overall loan book.

news.title: Homebuyers don't get timely help from Rajasthan RERA
news.para: According to the rules prescribed under the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016, authority must dispose of complaints within the stipulated period of 60 days. However, there are instances where homebuyers are waiting for months and still their complaint has not been resolved.

news.title: Smartworld Developers raises Rs 250 crore from Motilal Oswal
news.para: Smartworld Developers, which has been set up by promoters of M3M Group in 2021, in October last year announced an investment of around Rs 3,000 crore to develop the company's first two residential projects in Gurugram.

news.title: Housing market will continue to remain buoyant: Sundaram Home Finance
news.para: The city-based company has drawn up plans to expand into tier II and III cities in the south with the opening of 10 new branches by March 2023 to disburse business loans to small entrepreneurs, managing director Lakshminarayanan Duraiswamy said.

news.title: Secunderabad to verify drone data on properties
news.para: This survey is expected to complete within six weeks. SCB has also launched a mobile application to upload the survey data during the survey, the SCB official said.
